The paper discusses the development and evaluation of visual interfaces for digital libraries, which involves information retrieval (IR) and human-computer interaction (HC) aspects. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.HC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of standardized corpora and fixed tasks, which are common in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), suggesting cs.CL as a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for comparability of evaluation results, which is relevant to machine learning (ML) and data mining (DM), indicating cs.LG as another possible sub-category.
